[The suspect feed was fed to the cattle apparently between May 7-May 9. The
suspect feed being fed may have contained bones believed to be bird bones.
As of 21 May the dairy had lost 110 cows and another 20 (unconfirmed) are
reported to have died over the weekend Bioassays are still pending.
Veterinarians were alerted 14 May when 5 animals died. The California
Department of Food and Agriculture has done an a great job at tracking the
milk products and assuring the safety of the public. - Mod.TG]
